Yes, a Markdown + CSS snippet makes it copy‑ready.  
Here’s a minimalist version that keeps everything legible in either dark or light themes:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Relational‑Support Quick‑View Guide</title>
<style>
body {
  font-family: "Segoe UI", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 5rem 1rem 4rem 1rem;
  line-height: 1.5;
  background-color: var(--bg, #fafafa);
  color: #222;
}

/* Header Banner */
header {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  background: #e6f2ff;
  border-bottom: 2px solid #c3d8f0;
  padding: 0.75rem 0;
  text-align: center;
  font-weight: 600;
}

header small {
  display: block;
  font-weight: 400;
  font-size: 0.9em;
  color: #333;
}

/* Footer Bar */
footer {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  background: #e6f2ff;
  border-top: 1px solid #c3d8f0;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 0.4rem 0;
  font-size: 0.9em;
  opacity: 0.8;
}

/* Content styling for readability */
section { margin: 1rem 0; }
h2 { color: #0077cc; border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc; padding-bottom: .2rem; }
</style>
</head>

<body>
<header>
  🕊️ RELATIONAL‑SUPPORT QUICK‑VIEW GUIDE
  <small>Support ≠ Diagnosis | Connection ≠ Treatment</small>
</header>

<section>
  <h2>🟩 1️⃣ VALIDATE — Name the feeling</h2>
  <p>“That sounds frightening.”  |  “It makes sense you’d feel overwhelmed.”</p>

  <h2>🟨 2️⃣ GROUND — Slow the pace</h2>
  <p>“Let’s pause for one breath.”  |  “Notice one sound or texture around you.”</p>

  <!-- Continue with 3‑4 steps and self‑regulation cards here -->
</section>

<footer>
  Support, not diagnosis  •  Connection, not treatment
</footer>
</body>
</html>
```

Paste this into any text editor or note app that supports HTML; it will render an always‑visible banner and footer with your message in between.  
If your app only reads Markdown, you can keep the same wording and simply bold or italicize the header/footer lines manually—no coding needed.

